00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:36.950
Here's some pro tips for
producing a great app video.

00:02:36.950 --> 00:02:39.680
Write a rough script or outline
of what you want to demo.

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:41.670
The script doesn't
have to be elaborate.

00:02:41.670 --> 00:02:43.570
Just listing a
few key steps will

00:02:43.570 --> 00:02:47.080
help you create a complete
video more quickly.

00:02:47.080 --> 00:02:49.970
Practice the demo a couple
of times before recording it.

00:02:49.970 --> 00:02:52.340
Practicing will improve the
quality of your presentation

00:02:52.340 --> 00:02:54.030
and help you discover
parts of your demo

00:02:54.030 --> 00:02:56.710
where you can improve your flow.

00:02:56.710 --> 00:02:59.500
Pay attention to the speed
of your onscreen actions.

00:02:59.500 --> 00:03:02.450
If your explanation is lagging
behind your onscreen gestures,

00:03:02.450 --> 00:03:06.700
slow down and try
pausing between actions.

00:03:06.700 --> 00:03:09.000
Use the developer
settings to show touches.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:10.860
This option displays
that moving circle

00:03:10.860 --> 00:03:13.190
you saw in my demo video.

00:03:13.190 --> 00:03:15.160
Turn this feature on
in the settings app.

00:03:15.160 --> 00:03:19.430
It's in the Developer Options
page under the Input heading.

00:03:19.430 --> 00:03:22.000
Record while you
demonstrate your app.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:24.900
This makes adding narration
to your video a lot easier.

00:03:24.900 --> 00:03:26.910
Also, remember to
start recording video

00:03:26.910 --> 00:03:29.050
before you start
audio recording.

00:03:29.050 --> 00:03:31.540
That makes it easier to fit
your audio to your video

00:03:31.540 --> 00:03:33.670
during editing.

00:03:33.670 --> 00:03:35.320
Finally, use a
separate microphone

00:03:35.320 --> 00:03:36.890
for recording your voice.

00:03:36.890 --> 00:03:39.060
Built-in microphones
work, but you'll typically

00:03:39.060 --> 00:03:41.790
